<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,744,1165]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,780,806]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Corallum sparsely to densely branched; stem and branches pinnulate. Pinnules simple (without subpinnules); arranged bilaterally in two rows and also alternately. Spines smooth, triangular and compressed to conical, usually simple, but sometimes bifurcated and forming double spines; up to about 
<quantity box="[1160,1246,852,879]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
tall on the polyp side of the axis. Polyps up to 
<quantity box="[481,546,888,914]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
in transverse diameter; arranged uniserially on branches and pinnules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,744,1165]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,575,922,949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">
Species assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opresko &amp; Stewart &amp; Voza &amp; Tracey &amp; Brugler" authorityYear="2022" box="[437,575,922,949]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Diplopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[437,575,922,949]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">Diplopathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. Three species are assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opresko &amp; Stewart &amp; Voza &amp; Tracey &amp; Brugler" authorityYear="2022" box="[934,1071,923,949]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Diplopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[934,1071,923,949]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">Diplopathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this report: 
<taxonomicName authority="Opresko &amp; Stewart &amp; Voza &amp; Tracey &amp; Brugler, 2022" authorityName="Opresko &amp; Stewart &amp; Voza &amp; Tracey &amp; Brugler" authorityYear="2022" box="[1244,1394,923,949]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Diplopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="antarctica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1244,1264,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1280,1394,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">antarctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="4" pageNumber="35" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Opresko &amp; Stewart &amp; Voza &amp; Tracey &amp; Brugler, 2022" authorityName="Opresko &amp; Stewart &amp; Voza &amp; Tracey &amp; Brugler" authorityYear="2022" box="[215,393,959,985]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Diplopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="multipinnata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[215,235,960,985]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[250,393,959,985]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">multipinnata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[401,492,959,985]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[401,492,959,985]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Opresko &amp; Stewart &amp; Voza &amp; Tracey &amp; Brugler, 2022" authorityName="Opresko &amp; Stewart &amp; Voza &amp; Tracey &amp; Brugler" authorityYear="2022" box="[555,728,959,985]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Diplopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="tuatoruensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[555,575,960,985]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[590,728,960,985]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">tuatoruensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[736,827,959,985]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[736,827,959,985]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The major characters used to differentiate the species are the length of the pinnules, the size of the spines, and the density of the branching of the corallum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="35" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,744,1165]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1031,1057]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">Distribution.</emphasis>
The genus is at present known from the Lord Howe Rise in the SW Pacific and from the Ross Sea in the Southern Ocean (Pacific Antarctic Ridge region inside 60 
<superScript attach="left" box="[866,874,1067,1081]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">o</superScript>
South).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,744,1165]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1103,1129]" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name is derived from the Greek 
<emphasis box="[817,899,1103,1129]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">diploos</emphasis>
meaning “double” or “twofold”, referring to the two rows of pinnules, and the standard suffix 
<emphasis box="[663,736,1139,1165]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">pathes</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
